On Mon, Jan 18, 1999 at 12:57:09PM +1100, Steve Gardner wrote:
> 
> According to my analysis, Officers are now earning 1 VT/week, which they
> will be paid at the beginning of Februrary. The Distributor is earning 1
> VT/week, which should be paid weekly.

In that case, I shall increase the Tariff again.

Actually, I'm not sure about the legitimacy of the last setting. I did 
it on Saturday, well after the midnight Thursday cut-off time, and I'm
not really sure if the rule allows changes made after Thursday, and
before the beginning of the next week.

Now how much should I set it to?

Lessee... with the current arrangement of Offices, we have 8 Officers
getting a total of 13 BOS, plus 7 unemployed getting 3.5 BOS, thus we
are paying out a total of 16.5 VTs/week. Plus the Distributor's wage,
is 17.5 VTs/week.

Let's say that we will continue to distribute only about 2 Proposals
a week. And half the Players vote on them. That's 15 * Voting Tariff
a week. 17.5 / 15 = 1.16666 - for the sake of a little bit of scarcity,
I'll round up to 1.2 VTs. I won't push for quite as much scarcity as I
would have before, as now our current holdings are a good deal smaller
relative to the BOS.

I hereby set the Voting Tariff to 1.2VTs. This will come into effect
on Proposals distributed from next week onwards.

Blob

PS: Something interesting to be noted here: the nett payout of salaries
depends on the distribution of Offices. The smaller the group of players
who control the Officers, the more unemployment benefits need to be paid,
so the greater the outflow.

